set_temp_variable.description:
Sets a temporary variable's value to the specified amount, creating it if not defined. Temporary variables exist only for the duration of the current effect/trigger block and are not persisted. They are unscoped (the same everywhere) and can be modified in triggers.

**Example:**
```paradox
set_temp_variable = {
    temp_var = ROOT.overlord
}
```

```paradox
set_temp_variable = { my_temp_var = 1 }
```

